I want to re-iterate a warning!
Jun 2012 ‚Ä¢ Friends
I just want to re-issue a warning about kayaking in Halong Bay. My experience was in 2009 but I don't see enough about the dangers in the Bay area. I travelled with a friend and we arranged our Halong Bay Boat trip through a local operator on Cat Bah island. The boat was fine as was the intended programme which included the use of a kayak that we took with us. The kayaking turned into a nightmare because we were sucked into a cave that looked just like the many caverns at the bottom of the limestone karats that are generally only a metre deep. We capsized and were dragged into complete darkness in a very strong current, lost the kayak and fought for our lives, trying to drag ourselves along the cave walls against the current towards what we hoped was the exit. Rescue was slow to come; anyone less of a strong swimmer might have drowned.

The greatest shock came though when nobody really cared about our trauma or injuries but we were instead maltreated because we had lost the kayak. There was a demand for 500 US dollars on the spot and when we refused to pay (or couldn't because we didn't have so much cash on us) we were held to ransom on the boat. Only by phoning the guy we had arranged the tour through were we eventually let back on land and the drama continued until a day or so later when we got our passports back in Hanoi.
I won't say don't go to Halong Bay - it is beautiful but be weary of the kayaking. There was no warning and our boat crew clearly did not know about the danger either.
Written May 9, 2013
Richard B
Chester58 contributions
Paradise luxury cruises - excellent
Apr 2012 ‚Ä¢ Couples
We did a 2 night 3 day cruise with Paradise Cruises. I would recommend doing the 2 night rather than the 1 night as the drive from Hanoi is 4 hours, I think an 8 hour round trip for 20 hours on a boat would not be ideal.
The Paradise Luxury junk was excellent. We had an upper room with a balcony, which was small but functional (not much room on the boat for huge rooms). The food on the boat was excellent, and the staff were very good and helpful. My bag got misplaced, and they worked hard to find it, although I was panicking for a while. The sundeck on the top was nice with plenty of sunbeds.
On the first day we went to surprise cave, the main surprise was that it was rammed full of other people so was a slow queue through the cave and that it was pretty much ruined by too many people. Unless you are desperate to see the cave this would be a good time on the sundeck (I don't think they go here every day). On the next stop we were at Titov island. Some people went up to the observatory and said it was interesting, we kayaked to the beach, which was a nice trip.
Overnight all of the junks park up together. The evening meal was nice, but after that the boat has little life and they put a film on. We could hear some of the other junks partying. If you want a party boat probably not for you, but for a quiet time this is ideal.
On the second day we were moved onto the day boat, which for fine for the time we spent on it, and it had a bar and sundeck. On Cat Ba island we cycled to a village and went for a walk in the jungle. After going back to the day boat we went to an area of islands were we could kayak through some caves into otherwise inaccessible lagoons, these were spectacular.
Next day we had a quick rowing boat visit and then off back to port. Overall very good cruise, and well worth the visit.
Written April 29, 2012
norhellia
